The Makhado Library, together with Guyo Book Service in Louis Trichardt, will be holding an exhibition and conduct a programme to celebrate World Book Day on Monday (23 April). The event starts at 14:00 and should end by16:00. It aims to celebrate books by cultivating a culture of reading. The organisers have invited a number of people who are actively involved in the book industry. A renowned publisher and award-winning author and bookseller, Rudzani Tshianane, will be there as well as poet and lecturer Vonani Bila. Leigh-Ann Lendon from Protea Boekhuis has also indicated that she will be available to assist potential authors. A group from Timbila Reading Club will also grace the event. The event is open to the general public and the organisers encourage pupils and students and language teachers to attend.